<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[824,1475,376,688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis box="[862,917,377,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Notes</emphasis>
. – This taxon is a new record for the 
<collectingRegion box="[1309,1471,376,400]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="CLERC" box="[824,981,408,432]" firstAuthor="CLERC" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="107 - 127" refId="ref7586" refString="CLERC, P. (2011). Usnea. In: THELL, A. &amp; R. MOBERG (ed.), Nordic Lichen Fl. 4: 107 - 127. Dexter." type="journal article" year="2011">CLERC (2011)</bibRefCitation>
considered it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1329,1474,408,432]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="glabrescens">
<emphasis box="[1329,1474,408,432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. glabrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because there are many intermediate forms, especially in North America. However, in Europe, most of the specimens can be reliably identified to one or the other varieties, justifying their acceptance. 
<taxonomicName authority="var. glabrescens" box="[948,1276,536,560]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="glabrescens" variety="glabrescens">
<emphasis box="[948,1123,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">Usnea glabrescens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1169,1276,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">glabrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has well delimited circular soralia that are not at all or little excavate whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[824,1145,600,624]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="glabrescens" variety="fulvoreagens">
<emphasis box="[824,967,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. glabrescens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1018,1145,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">fulvoreagens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has distinctly excavate 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Parmeliaceae" genus="Usnea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lapponica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="172">U. lapponica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like soralia. See 
<bibRefCitation author="CLERC" box="[1060,1207,632,656]" firstAuthor="CLERC" pageId="7" pageNumber="172" pagination="302 - 335" refId="ref7532" refString="CLERC, P. (2007). Usnea. In: NASH III, T., C. GRIES &amp; F. BUNGARTZ (ed.), Lich. Fl. Gr. Sonoran Desert Region 3: 302 - 335. Lichens Unlimited, Arizona State University, Tempe." type="journal article" year="2007">CLERC (2007)</bibRefCitation>
for a detailed description of this taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
